{"word":"ναυστολέω","slug":"ναυστολέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ναυστολέω</b></el> <el>(ναυστολέω,) ( φυτ. <el>-ήσω</el>) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ναύστολος'><el>ναύστολος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><a href='S:transitive'>trans.</a> <i>to carry</i> or <i>convey by sea</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, with <a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>mid.</a> <el>-ήσομαι</el>, <i>to go by sea</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to guide, steer</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>: <a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a>, <el>τὼ πτέρυγε ποῖ ναυστολεῖς</el>; whither <i>pliest thou</i> thy wings? <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:intransitive'>intr.</a> like <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to go by ship, sail</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>generally, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> loci, <i>to travel over</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}